items.name: AI Beast Mix
items.description:
ABOUT

AI Beast Mix is a model merge to achieve semi-realism result for furry character with NSFW kink such as muscle or hyper. The model also can generate several style as well. Sometime the model generate human character which can be prevent by specify the furry species. If you're into hyper, this model capable support those kink and even work well with lot loras and lycoris. Prompt properly and this model will work wonders. prompt works well with e621 prompt tag.

Also, Hires.Fix is recommended to get better details and result.

Which one to Download?

Pruned fp16 - Suitable if you feel like to generate image only. May lack some data but still close enough generate image like full model. Good for those want to save disk space.

Full Model fp32 - Normal and Heavy model but contain all the data that you can use to merge with other model. Feel free to use this model to make your own mix.

VERSION 1.7

Unsatisfied with version 1.6, I decide to find a way to improve it. This version 1.7 is a direct upgrade from version 1.6 which it will add more small details and sharpening the image if possible. This time I attempt with different model merge method where I juggle merge between 3 or more models at one point to make it more precise to my liking. There also additional model have been merge into this model so some not working lora might possibly works. There also VAE baked during model merge process so I'm not sure to consider VAE as included because I have merge it with another model after the VAE bake. Anyway, I hope this version is fun to use to generate images

version 1.4 - merge lot of model with proper merge order and structure

version 1.5 - change model merge method for better result

items.name: L666 (LoRA)
items.description:
This is the LoRA version of my L666 model. You have the flexibility to create lingerie-clad girls with any model you choose (though it seems to work very well with F222.)

I recommend starting with a strength of 1.0 and adjusting as needed depending on your model, prompt, etc.

This model supports most Danbooru tags related to people, women, fashion, lingerie, etc.

Recommended tags:

  • Asian or European. If you specify Asian, you'll get Asian girls. If you specify European, you'll get white girls. If you don't specify either, you might get either or mixed-race girls. Although the model wasn't trained on other races, I've been able to prompt for them (i.e. black girls) but you may need to add "Asian" and/or "European" to the negative prompt for best results.

  • bra, panties, underwear, etc: that's the main thing this model is trained to produce.

  • good aesthetic, good quality, good blur, good noise, good contrast - Put any or all of these in your prompt if you want to the image to look better. Note: I've programmatically labeled images this way, similar to how WD1.5 was trained.

  • pntyad: Some of the images were trained on lingerie/panty ads which may result in higher quality images but with a greater possibility of watermarks, text, signatures, and other artifacts appearing. Highly recommended that you add the appropriate negative prompt.

  • (Negative Prompt): poor aesthetic, poor quality, poor blur, poor noise, poor contrast -Put any of these in your negative prompt if your images aren't looking as great.

  • (Negative Prompt): bad-hands-5 - this textual inversion seems to work very well when you're not getting great hands.

  • (Negative Prompt): bad_prompt - similarly, this textual inversion works great when you're not getting properly formed limbs.

  • (Negative Prompt): text, logo, signature, username, watermark - A lot of images in the training set contained logos and watermarks so you'll want these in the negative prompt.

items.name: Background Complexity Additive
items.description:
This model is meant to enhanced the complexity and prominence of your backgrounds. It's made by combining background-focused loras and then target isolating blocks to reduce the effect on things like style, clothing, coloring, anatomy, or facial details.

In practice it's a bit finicky. The primary observed effect it that without any tags for shot distance, it will make your background take up more space. It won't necessarily make your background better, persay, but will increase the number of visible background elements, their density, and their prominence. In the case of images where you want one extremely prominent backdrop or you want your character to be silhouetted against the backdrop it actually might be better not to prompt it or prompt it negative, as prompting it negative will creat the opposite effect. Because of the way it's block isolated, you can prompt it at strong weights without it making your picture look like a complete mess. I recommend toying with both positive and negative weights if you decide to use it, as both create interesting outcomes.

If you prompt for an image that only has landscape/scenery, prompting it will increase coherency. Likewise, negative prompting it will make the landscape make less sense. Both have their own uses.

items.name: XenoEngine 6th Sense
items.description:
This model should be considered "Beta" - and, as such, there will likely be a bit of instability with certain things you're trying to do but that I haven't gotten conceptually trained well enough.

This checkpoint is the result of my desire to make highly capable yet simple to prompt models that will produce consistent output. The "simple to prompt" bit is working pretty well, here, but there's some room for improvement in the "consistent output" department. Put someone in a different scenario and their style and look can start to change. Calling for a specific style can help - but I'll also be working on getting this working better in future updates.

By default, this model produces a sort of semi-real analog photo/IRAY Render, with a hint of dreaminess. Mostly.

Like it? Buy me a beer.

This model has been merged and trained with various other trained models and LoRa's. I'll be updating this post with notes on some of the trigger phrases that are working well and that are somewhat unique to this model. Check back in a day or two.

When combining these trained models, I lowered their influence a bit to ensure that they didn't take over all the time. As such, you sometimes need to increase the weight just a smidge to get things working. (e.g. (Vulcan:1.2) Ambassador).

Subreddit: This will often make your subjects get a more "amateur model" look - but then again, that's often what we're going for. Don't forget to prefect the tokens with r/ (e.g. r/girlsgonewild).

Species: This one is a lot of fun! Some don't work particularly well, but others are way cool.

Luna's Angels: Does a nice job of ethnicity related skin colors (and seems to have helped unlock skin colors from "species" and maybe some other places, too. I'm really excited about how well this works - getting ethnicities is always hard and, with the models I've used, getting a dark skinned beauty is tough... it's a bit easier now, hopefully.

VR Porn: Has a few sexual positions that work fairly well. Call your sexual partner on most of them or you'll have disembodied genitals and whatnot. lol

modelVersions.name: v6.1
modelVersions.description:
This is primarily a sanity update... the original release was really cool because it did a lot of things that most other models don't do at all, but it also ended up breaking/distoriting a lot of the cool things it was trying to do.

With this version, we've backed of some of the training items in favor of locking in on one good set, and then moving on to the next.

As such - some of the triggers mentioned in the main notes may not work as well anymore - while others will maybe work a bit better - at least the ones that worked fairly well from the start.

items.name: Space elevator太空电梯
items.description:
以前说到科幻，我一般都会想到美国大片，漫威宇宙。但是现在我会想到流浪地球，太空电梯的长镜头太棒了，本模型使用了小破球2的画面为素材训练而成，如果你还在遗憾京哥没邀请你参演小破球，没关系。现在你可以使用这个lora个人客串了，后面有空了我再给郭导打个电话，让他授权吧，目前还没有，请大家自娱自乐，不要用于任何商业用途。

权重:0.5~1。其中0.8~1是纯建筑，想要加人的话建议在0.7以下。

通过BRA和majimix两个模型的测试，泛用性很不错，训练用的底膜是raRender_v20

我的本意是生成破球风的建筑，但是在跑实例图的时候想到 没有人的模型毫无意义。于是我添加了1girl，结果不但加人，还能生成人机结合体，本人提示词比较偷懒，请发挥你的想象力，可以生成更多的惊喜。

地面基地，空中轨道，空间站都在训练范围内。

When it comes to science fiction, I usually think of American blockbusters, Marvel Universe. But now I will think of the wandering earth, the long lens of the Space elevator is great. This model uses the picture of Little Broken Ball 2 as the material for training. If you still regret that Brother Jing didn't invite you to play Little Broken Ball, it doesn't matter. Now you can use this Lora personal guest appearance. When I have time later, I will call Director Guo and ask him to authorize it. Currently, it is not yet available. Please enjoy yourself and do not use it for any commercial purposes.

Weight: 0.5-1. Among them, 0.8~1 are pure buildings, and it is recommended to add people below 0.7.

Through the testing of BRA and Majimix models, the universality is very good, and the training substrate is raRender_ V20

My original intention was to create a building with a futuristic style, but when running the example diagram, it was meaningless to think of a model without anyone. So I added 1Girl, and the result is not only adding people, but also generating a human-machine combination. My prompt is quite lazy, please use your imagination to generate more surprises.

The ground base, air orbit, and space station are all within the training range.

items.name: Frostblade Irelia | League of Legends
items.description:
LoRA trained on the Frostblade Irelia from League of Legends

requested by @Edenwari

tags: frostblade irelia, 1girl, short hair, blue hair, bodysuit, detached sleeves

models used

anime: Sweet-mix - v1.8 - flat, teste1

2,5D: ReV Animated, PastelDiffusedMix - V2.1, CuriousMerge 2.5D - v4.0 Experimental

realistic: Paragon V1.0

negative embeddings: bad_prompt, negative_hand, ng_deepnegative_v1_75t, bad-artist, EasyNegative

Recommended settings:

  • Make sure you are aware on the usage instructions of LORA

  • VAE: vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned (for realistic models & 2,5D), kl-f8-anime2, blessed2.vae (for anime models)

  • Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras or DPM++ 2M Karras(euler a for img2img upscaling) from time to time im also using DPM++ 2M alt Karras

  • Steps: 20 to 35

  • Clipskip: 2

  • Upscaler : GitHub - pkuliyi2015/multidiffusion-upscaler-for-automatic1111 4x-UltraSharp(for 2,5D & realistic), 4xAnimesharp(for anime)

  • CFG Scale : 5 to 9 (mostly 7)

  • LORA weight for txt2img: 0.5-1 (for the examples i mostly used 0.8 and 1)

  • Denoise strength upscaling: 0.3 to 0.55

for full body shots i recommend using: ComfyUI Impact Pack

or the a1111 alternative GitHub - Bing-su/adetailer

items.name: Margaux Cipher
items.description:
Margaux Cipher is a person who doesn't exist. You can use her if you need a consistent character.

Please have a look at other Nobody models for contributions by other folks including those created with the LastName and NBDY tags.

Follow me if you'd like to be notified of future models!

Installation

To install, download the .bin file and then place in the stable-diffusion-webui/embeddings/ folder. Then you'll either need to restart WebUI or tap the Refresh button in the Textual Inversions tab in the Extra Networks tab.

To Use

The trigger word is MargauxCipher which you can use in your prompt. See the gallery below for some examples. For InvokeAI it should be <margauxcipher>

A note about what I use to generate images

  • My main go-to photorealistic models right now are RealisticVision 2.0 and ICBINP.

  • I always use the vae-ft-mse-840000 as my VAE. You can find it at HuggingFace. You can enable the VAE dropdown menu in WebUI by going to Settings -> User Interface -> Quicksettings list and adding "sd_vae"

  • To upscale I'll use a combination of ControlNet 1.1's tile_resample/tile model and Ultimate SD Upscaler
